The paper deals with a theoretical analysis of a stochastic model of self-assembly, which involves the study of algorithms and complexity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which deals with combinatorial structures and algorithms. The paper also involves lower bounds on time complexity, which suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science). The paper also discusses the application of the model to macroscale robotic systems, which suggests categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
